            "resource": {
                "@type": "dctypes:Text",
                "format": "text/html",
                "chars": "<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-inline-start: 48px;\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: circle; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: 36pt;\" aria-level=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">J. S. James&rsquo;s </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: #ffff00; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">historical note for RESTORATION in </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: #ffff00; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Union Harp and History of Songs</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: #ffff00; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> (1909) includes biographical entries </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">on Newton and Everett that characterize the singers&rsquo; facility with and preferences among different shape-note systems and songbooks,</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: #ffff00; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> information he excluded from the version of the note that appeared in </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: #ffff00; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Original Sacred Harp</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: #ffff00; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">. </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">This tune was re-arranged by Professor T. B. Newton and Dr. S. W. Everett. Professor Newton is from Milton County, Ga. He has been teaching four shaped notes. [In Original Sacred Harp, James replaced the preceding sentence with the following: &ldquo;He has been teaching music in Georgia and adjoining states for fifty years, and he is a great admirer of the old Sacred Harp songs.&rdquo;] He has a fine voice, perfectly clear and mellow and sings every time opportunity presents itself. He is almost in perfect health and is 72 years of age. He has taught thousands of people to sing, and no man can be found that enjoys life better than he. He has spent his life in the field of music. </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Dr. S. W. Everett resides in Newton County, Georgia. He, too, is a fine singer, and </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: #ffff00; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">his choice is the four shaped notes, yet he sings out of all books</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">. Both Professor Newton and Dr. Everett </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: #ffff00; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">are strict members of the Primitive Baptist church</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">. Both of them helped to arrange the United Sacred Harp Musical Association, and belong to many other musical conventions and societies. [UHHS185]</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>",
                "language": "en"
            },
